       BA000	       SECTION 60.
       BA00.
	     MOVE "Access Key Error"
				 TO WS-ERR-TYPE.
	     EVALUATE WS-STAT2
	       WHEN "1"
		   MOVE "Sequence error"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
	       WHEN "2"
		   MOVE "Duplicate key"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
		   MOVE WS-DUPLICATE
				 TO WS-RESULT
		   MOVE 2	 TO LS-ERROR
		   GO TO BA05
	       WHEN "3"
		   MOVE "No record found"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
		   MOVE 3	 TO LS-ERROR
		   MOVE WS-RECOVER
				 TO WS-RESULT
		   GO TO BA05
	       WHEN "4"
		   MOVE "Boundry violation"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
	     END-EVALUATE.
	     MOVE 99		 TO LS-ERROR.
	     MOVE WS-FATAL	 TO WS-RESULT.


       BA05.
	     PERFORM AA100.

       BA999.
	     EXIT.
      *
      *    ****    P E R M A N E N T   E R R O R
      *
       CA000	       SECTION 61.
       CA00.
	     MOVE "Permanent Error"
				 TO WS-ERR-TYPE.
	     EVALUATE WS-STAT2
	       WHEN "0"
		   MOVE "DISK error"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
	       WHEN "4"
		   MOVE "Boundry violation"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
	       WHEN "5"
		   MOVE "File not found"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
	       WHEN "7"
		   MOVE "Open mode not supported"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
	       WHEN "8"
		   MOVE "File locked"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
		   MOVE 12	 TO LS-ERROR
		   MOVE WS-RECOVER
				 TO WS-RESULT
		   GO TO CA05
	       WHEN "9"
		   MOVE "File attributes error"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
	     END-EVALUATE.
	     MOVE 99		 TO LS-ERROR.
	     MOVE WS-FATAL	 TO WS-RESULT.

       CA05.
	     PERFORM AA100.

       CA999.
	     EXIT.
      *
      *    ****    L O G I C A L   E R R O R
      *
       DA000	       SECTION 62.
       DA00.
	     MOVE "Logical Error"
				 TO WS-ERR-TYPE.
	     EVALUATE WS-STAT2
	       WHEN "1"
		   MOVE "File already open"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
		   MOVE 4	 TO LS-ERROR
		   MOVE WS-RECOVER
				 TO WS-RESULT
		   GO TO DA10
	       WHEN "2"
		   MOVE "File already closed"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
		   MOVE 5	 TO LS-ERROR
		   MOVE WS-RECOVER
				 TO WS-RESULT
		   GO TO DA10
	       WHEN "3"
		   MOVE "Previous Read unsuccessfull"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
		   MOVE 3	 TO LS-ERROR
		   MOVE WS-RECOVER
				 TO WS-RESULT
		   GO TO DA10
	       WHEN "4"
		   MOVE "Boundry violation"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
	       WHEN "5"
		   MOVE "Record size error"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
	       WHEN "6"
		   MOVE "No next record available"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
		   MOVE 3	 TO LS-ERROR
		   MOVE WS-RECOVER
				 TO WS-RESULT
		   GO TO DA10
	       WHEN "7"
		   MOVE "File not open for input"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
		   MOVE 10	 TO LS-ERROR
		   MOVE WS-RECOVER
				 TO WS-RESULT
		   GO TO DA10
	       WHEN "8"
		   MOVE "File not open for output"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
		   MOVE 11	 TO LS-ERROR
		   MOVE WS-RECOVER
				 TO WS-RESULT
		   GO TO DA10
	       WHEN "9"
		   MOVE "File not open as IO"
				 TO WS-STAT-MESSAGE
		   MOVE 14	 TO LS-ERROR
		   MOVE WS-RECOVER
				 TO WS-RESULT
		   GO TO DA10
	     END-EVALUATE.
	     MOVE 99		 TO LS-ERROR.
	     MOVE WS-FATAL	 TO WS-RESULT.

       DA10.
	     PERFORM AA100.

       DA999.
